Korean localization scope:
- Practice profile (CLAUDE.md) re-authored for the Korean Personal
  Information Protection Act (PIPA) and related laws.
- Skill prompts (skills/*/SKILL.md) re-authored to reference Korean
  statutes, regulators (PIPC, KISA), case law, and practice norms.
- MCP connector set replaced: Western legal-research connectors
  (CourtListener, Westlaw, Ironclad) removed; the korean-law MCP
  (https://mcp.gomdori.app/law), backed by the Korean Ministry of
  Government Legislation (법제처) National Law Information open API
  (https://open.law.go.kr), added as the primary statute and
  case-law source.
- Two new KR-specific skills added (pipa-spi-handling, cross-border-transfer).
- All retained guardrail patterns (work-product header, source attribution
  tags, decision posture, jurisdiction recognition) carry their original
  intent into the Korean privilege and confidentiality regime, with
  Korean-equivalent terminology and a documented note that the US
  "attorney work product" doctrine does not exist in Korean law.

Data sources used at runtime by this plugin:
- korean-law MCP (https://mcp.gomdori.app/law) — provides Korean
  statutes, case law, constitutional decisions, administrative rules,
  local ordinances, treaties, interpretations, and committee decisions,
  sourced from the Korean Ministry of Government Legislation (법제처)
  National Law Information open API (https://open.law.go.kr). A free
  OC key is required. Outputs are reference material; not legal effect.
  Verify against primary sources before relying.

